	<h2>Apply Now For The Material Handler Position</h2>
	
	<h3>Material Handler</h3>

	<div class="category_det_align">
		<h3>About the Job</h3>

		<p>Around the world, hundreds of times a day, people touch and use our packaging.​ You would be surprised how often you interact with our products, when you open a bottle, unwrap a pack or tear open a pouch.​ We Apply art and science to create responsible packaging products, used by people around the world.​</p><br>

		<h3>Job Description:</h3>
		<p>This position will support all production operations to optimize output and minimize waste while maintaining excellent quality and safety standards.​</p><br>

		<h3>Job Summary:</h3>
		 <p>Responsible for the timely delivery and pick-up of material, to the production areas to meet scheduling and production needs to achieve production standards aligned with plant goals.​ Adhere to plant processes, safe operating methods, and good housekeeping standards</p><br>

		<h3>Principal Duties & Responsibilities:</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Demonstrate the proper use of a lift truck and maintain forklift license certification</li>
			<li>Deliver and return material substrates to the production equipment to meet scheduling and order requirements as needed.​</li>
			<li>Unload plant supplies</li>
			<li>Demonstrates effective interactive skills to support production and scheduling activities related to meet customer needs/​requirement, and plant goals</li>
		</ul>
		<br>

		<h3>Job Specifications:</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Package and wrap Finished Goods to specific Customer requirements</li>
			<li>Issue and receive raw and sub-assembly material to production floor</li>
			<li>Provide rollstock and pallets to production floor</li>
			<li>Manage,Assemble, monitor, and weigh production generated scrap gaylords</li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<h3>Specialized Knowledge/​Skills:</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Bringing the correct manufacturing material to the line</li>
			<li>Returning material to the correct storage location & properly labelling when applicable</li>
			<li>Putting subassemblies away in the racks and properly status product and bays</li>
			<li>Maintaining corrugate returns and recyclables</li>
			<li>Good computer skills</li>
		 
			<li>Strong mechanical skills Strong Attendance and Safety Record</li>
			<li>Ability to stand and walk for majority of a 12 hour rotating shift</li>
			<li>Ability to read and speak English</li>
			<li>Ability to follow verbal and written directions</li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<h3>Requirements </h3>
		<h3>Education/​Experience:</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>High school diploma or GED, Associates Degree and/​or industrial certification preferred</li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<h3>Work Environment/​Physical Requirements:</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Physically able to lift 50 lbs</li>
			<li>Able to operate heavy machinery continuously</li>
			<li>Standing up to 12 hours per day on a rotating day or evening shift, up to 5 days per week</li>
			<li>Able to drive a forklift for up to 12 hours per day</li>
			<li>Occasional twisting, turning, or bending to move items up to 50 lbs</li>
			<li>Alert state of mind to avoid safety hazards</li>
		</ul>
